  "texts": [
    "This happens when all the exponents at ∞ of the initial connection are of slope > 1 (and, by the stationary phase formula, this is then the case for its Fourier transform as well).",
    "In order to have a cleaner description of the algorithm, we will make the following further simplifying assumptions (see Assumption 4.1 in Section 4):",
    "• The set of exponents at ∞ of the connection is of the form {az k | a ∈ A} for some fixed k ∈ Q >1 and some finite set A ⊂ C \\ {0} (where z is a local coordinate at 0), • |a| = |b| for any a, b ∈ A, i.e.",
    "all parameters lie on the same circle centred at the origin.",
    "Note that these assumptions are invariant under Fourier transformation: If a system satisfies all our hypotheses, its Fourier transform will do so, too."
  ],
